This paper presents a data compression and dimensionality reduction scheme for wireless sensor networks, which is a subfield of computer networking and falls under the category of cs.NI (Networks and Internet Architecture). The proposed approach uses unsupervised neural network schemes, namely autoencoders, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, indicating that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions an error bound guarantee mechanism, which suggests that it could be related to control systems and optimization, falling under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
